TEXT 928 -56 Left 0 ;Simple example with two components from the 74HC and CD4000 library. Both\nlibrarys contain digital circuits from two logic families. Both are CMOS. You can\nmix them also in real live.\nHere we have a JK-FF from the CD4000 series, and a D-FF from the 7400 family.\nTo use the two libraries you have to insert the '.lib' dot command:\n \n.lib 74HC.lib       and/or\n.lib CD4000.lib\n \nThe circuits from both libraries need 'power'. So you have to insert a voltage source. The \nnames of the voltage net must be different for both libraries. For the CD4000 you \nneed a 'VDD' symbol and for the 74HC a 'VCC' symbol. Use the 'Label Net' command.\nGround symbol as usual!\n \nThere are two other component available: 'DVIEW5' and 'DVIEW10'. These components\n'format' digital signals for the plot output. You will not see the real simulated signal but a\nshrinked nice aligned version. That makes it simpler to compare digital signals in the \nplot window. To use these components you have to include\n \n.lib dview.lib
